WEBVTT

00:00:17.930 --> 00:00:18.930
Wataru...

00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:22.900
Can we...?

00:00:37.390 --> 00:00:38.870
Goodnight.

00:00:41.980 --> 00:00:42.980
Wait.

00:00:46.060 --> 00:00:47.060
Wait, what...?

00:00:48.990 --> 00:00:49.990
Is he asleep?

00:00:50.390 --> 00:00:51.510
How can you sleep right now?

00:01:01.620 --> 00:01:02.620
I...

00:01:03.410 --> 00:01:06.660
I actually kissed Minato.

00:01:54.600 --> 00:01:56.500
"Countdown To Yes"

00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:04.800
(Episode 7)

00:02:05.970 --> 00:02:07.090
Wataru...

00:02:15.110 --> 00:02:16.160
Wataru...

00:02:16.590 --> 00:02:17.590
Can we...?

00:02:24.510 --> 00:02:25.510
Whoa!

00:02:31.130 --> 00:02:32.130
Huh?

00:02:32.420 --> 00:02:33.420
Where's the blanket?

00:02:34.250 --> 00:02:35.250
Oh...

00:02:35.990 --> 00:02:36.990
Sorry.

00:02:37.270 --> 00:02:38.370
I must've kicked it off.

00:02:39.980 --> 00:02:41.200
You've got a hell of a kick.

00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:46.790
Hmm?

00:02:47.220 --> 00:02:48.560
Oh, it's nothing.

00:02:49.600 --> 00:02:50.600
Wataru.

00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:51.600
Yeah?

00:02:52.650 --> 00:02:53.650
Good morning.

00:02:57.130 --> 00:02:58.130
Morning...

00:03:01.910 --> 00:03:03.250
Minato, about that...

00:03:03.550 --> 00:03:05.620
- About yesterday...
- I'm starving.

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:07.230
Let's have some yogurt.

00:03:08.210 --> 00:03:09.640
Wait, hold on.

00:03:19.090 --> 00:03:20.530
What kind of dream was that?

00:03:26.110 --> 00:03:27.110
And more importantly...

00:03:27.260 --> 00:03:28.260
Was I the one taking it?

00:03:43.010 --> 00:03:44.250
Do you want some too?

00:03:47.640 --> 00:03:50.040
How can you act like nothing happened?

00:03:50.740 --> 00:03:51.940
Wataru?

00:03:53.430 --> 00:03:54.430
Oh.

00:03:54.470 --> 00:03:55.670
Yeah, I'll have some.

00:04:03.080 --> 00:04:04.080
Here.

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:08.400
Thanks.

00:04:24.020 --> 00:04:25.020
Yesterday...

00:04:25.530 --> 00:04:28.040
I definitely kissed Minato, right?

00:04:29.140 --> 00:04:31.440
Was it really just a dream?

00:04:34.520 --> 00:04:35.520
But...

00:04:36.100 --> 00:04:37.590
I can still feel it right here.

00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:40.510
Wataru.

00:04:41.900 --> 00:04:42.900
Huh?

00:04:43.110 --> 00:04:44.040
What is it?

00:04:44.041 --> 00:04:45.510
You're off today too, right?

00:04:46.180 --> 00:04:47.180
Yeah.

00:04:47.570 --> 00:04:48.870
There's something I want to do.

00:04:50.540 --> 00:04:51.640
Something you want to do?

00:04:59.430 --> 00:05:01.650
- Sorry to keep you waiting.
- No worries.

00:05:04.130 --> 00:05:06.310
Minato, you're a fast drinker.

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:08.200
- You should try some.
- Okay.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:12.300
Alright, shall we get started?

00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:20.130
Sorry for the last-minute request.

00:05:20.370 --> 00:05:21.370
No, it's fine.

00:05:21.970 --> 00:05:23.290
So, what's the budget?

00:05:23.620 --> 00:05:25.780
I brought a few options with me.

00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:27.730
I need to talk it over with Wataru.

00:05:27.880 --> 00:05:28.880
Wait, why?

00:05:28.881 --> 00:05:30.521
Aren't you guys moving in together again?

00:05:30.680 --> 00:05:31.360
We are not.

00:05:31.361 --> 00:05:33.270
We're still just considering it.

00:05:33.430 --> 00:05:35.806
Leave it to me. I'll find
you guys a great place.

00:05:36.270 --> 00:05:38.740
Why are you taking his side?

00:05:39.580 --> 00:05:41.790
Because this counts toward my sales quota.

00:05:42.020 --> 00:05:43.299
Once you're in the real world,

00:05:43.300 --> 00:05:44.780
you realize groundwork is everything.

00:05:45.200 --> 00:05:46.200
Exactly.

00:05:46.490 --> 00:05:49.570
Now then, valued customers,

00:05:49.730 --> 00:05:51.900
what do you think of this property?

00:05:52.990 --> 00:05:54.870
It's a ten-minute walk from the station.

00:05:55.010 --> 00:05:56.589
The kitchen is huge.

00:05:56.590 --> 00:05:59.060
Plenty of room for two people to cook.

00:05:59.940 --> 00:06:00.940
That sounds nice.

00:06:01.010 --> 00:06:02.010
And...

00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:04.160
There's tons of storage.

00:06:04.550 --> 00:06:08.270
You'll have no problem
storing your camera gear.

00:06:09.170 --> 00:06:10.510
Storage is key.

00:06:11.060 --> 00:06:12.580
I guess that's true...

00:06:12.950 --> 00:06:13.950
Plus,

00:06:13.970 --> 00:06:15.810
the balcony is very spacious.

00:06:16.050 --> 00:06:17.610
You could grow some plants,

00:06:17.840 --> 00:06:19.370
or even put out a table and chairs.

00:06:19.490 --> 00:06:22.590
It's perfect for some "balcony time."

00:06:22.800 --> 00:06:24.260
I want to grow tomatoes.

00:06:24.940 --> 00:06:25.940
Balcony time?

00:06:27.060 --> 00:06:28.060
And wait, there's more!

00:06:28.140 --> 00:06:29.180
Since it's west-facing,

00:06:29.380 --> 00:06:31.600
the afternoon sun is lovely.

00:06:31.620 --> 00:06:33.640
It's the best spot for a nap.

00:06:34.910 --> 00:06:37.050
Though it might get a
bit hot in the summer.

00:06:37.880 --> 00:06:38.880
A nap...

00:06:41.530 --> 00:06:44.209
Also, it's a reinforced concrete structure,

00:06:44.210 --> 00:06:45.746
so it has excellent earthquake resistance.

00:06:45.770 --> 00:06:47.230
Safety is important.

00:06:47.670 --> 00:06:50.660
If I could live with Minato again...

00:06:57.140 --> 00:06:58.570
Wataru.

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:03.470
Wataru, wake up.

00:07:06.790 --> 00:07:08.550
Dinner's ready.

00:07:10.230 --> 00:07:11.230
Huh?

00:07:12.150 --> 00:07:14.230
Let's eat together.

00:07:20.710 --> 00:07:21.710
No!

00:07:26.980 --> 00:07:27.980
Wataru?

00:07:31.570 --> 00:07:32.570
What's wrong?

00:07:33.060 --> 00:07:34.060
Oh...

00:07:34.090 --> 00:07:35.090
No.

00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:36.160
It's nothing.

00:07:36.850 --> 00:07:37.850
I...

00:07:38.070 --> 00:07:39.810
I've been like this since this morning.

00:07:40.370 --> 00:07:41.829
Also, the landlord here

00:07:41.830 --> 00:07:44.940
is likely to approve
you even as just friends.

00:07:44.980 --> 00:07:45.980
We're not friends.

00:07:49.310 --> 00:07:50.760
I have something to do.

00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:51.950
I should probably head out.

00:07:52.360 --> 00:07:54.480
Wait, you have plans?

00:07:54.650 --> 00:07:57.410
Yes! Something very important.

00:08:14.490 --> 00:08:15.490
Thanks for today.

00:08:16.080 --> 00:08:17.080
Sure.

00:08:17.120 --> 00:08:20.070
Hey, let me know right
away if you like any of those.

00:08:20.470 --> 00:08:22.010
Yeah, I got it.

00:08:24.490 --> 00:08:25.490
You too, Wataru.

00:08:25.770 --> 00:08:27.000
Let's grab dinner sometime.

00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:29.740
Yeah.

00:08:30.140 --> 00:08:31.140
Okay.

00:08:31.430 --> 00:08:32.430
I'm off.

00:08:33.580 --> 00:08:34.740
Thanks.

00:08:37.970 --> 00:08:38.970
Wataru.

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:40.000
Wait, we need to...

00:08:43.840 --> 00:08:44.840
Wataru?

00:08:52.390 --> 00:08:53.390
Wataru, hold on.

00:08:55.130 --> 00:08:56.560
Wataru, I said wait!

00:09:00.720 --> 00:09:02.690
Why are you making decisions on your own?

00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:04.280
Was it too sudden?

00:09:04.281 --> 00:09:05.420
It was way too sudden.

00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:07.620
Looking at apartments
without even asking me?

00:09:09.850 --> 00:09:12.600
I just thought it'd be easier
to visualize if we saw some.

00:09:13.240 --> 00:09:15.550
And you almost told
him we weren't friends...

00:09:16.630 --> 00:09:18.230
Did you even think about how he'd react?

00:09:20.470 --> 00:09:21.600
I didn't.

00:09:23.180 --> 00:09:25.720
If he wants to distance himself
because of that, I don't care.

00:09:27.810 --> 00:09:29.609
Well, I care. It's not okay.

00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:30.610
Wataru?

00:09:35.060 --> 00:09:36.880
I told you I wanted us to be best friends.

00:09:42.800 --> 00:09:44.590
Then why did you say we could kiss?

00:09:47.400 --> 00:09:48.400
We can...

00:09:59.220 --> 00:10:00.150
That was...

00:10:00.151 --> 00:10:01.680
We clearly like each other.

00:10:02.970 --> 00:10:05.530
I don't get why you're so
hung up on being "best friends."

00:10:10.810 --> 00:10:13.320
Because to me, our
friendship is more important.

00:10:14.500 --> 00:10:15.880
That's just what I don't get.

00:10:24.350 --> 00:10:27.110
Someone once told me that people
only forgive because they're in love.

00:10:28.080 --> 00:10:29.080
Huh?

00:10:32.100 --> 00:10:33.510
When it comes to photography,

00:10:34.060 --> 00:10:35.850
I tend to tune everything else out.

00:10:37.040 --> 00:10:38.630
And all my other flaws...

00:10:40.490 --> 00:10:41.840
Is this about your ex?

00:10:45.670 --> 00:10:48.270
She said she only put up with me
because of her "romantic filter."

00:10:49.420 --> 00:10:50.420
Filter...?

00:10:54.370 --> 00:10:55.370
But...

00:10:55.700 --> 00:10:57.020
Even without something like that,

00:10:57.290 --> 00:10:59.480
you already know all my bad sides, Minato.

00:11:00.070 --> 00:11:01.620
Isn't that because we're best friends?

00:11:02.640 --> 00:11:04.929
Wataru, I think you're missing the point...

00:11:04.930 --> 00:11:06.320
I don't even know anymore.

00:11:13.680 --> 00:11:15.190
Even if we live together again,

00:11:16.150 --> 00:11:17.950
you'll just be the first
one to leave anyway.

00:11:19.310 --> 00:11:21.850
- I'm not leaving again.
- How can you be sure?

00:11:22.420 --> 00:11:24.540
Can you promise you'll
never be transferred for work?

00:11:26.330 --> 00:11:27.330
Well...

00:11:32.080 --> 00:11:33.490
Just like with your photography,

00:11:35.270 --> 00:11:36.690
you'll leave me behind again.

00:11:46.410 --> 00:11:47.410
I...

00:11:48.990 --> 00:11:51.540
I truly want to support you
from the bottom of my heart.

00:11:52.340 --> 00:11:54.100
I want you to follow
the path you've chosen.

00:11:57.210 --> 00:12:00.190
But I can't do it...

00:12:04.440 --> 00:12:05.910
I can't help wanting you by my side.

00:12:07.280 --> 00:12:08.980
I'd just be so lonely.

00:12:14.230 --> 00:12:17.379
It feels like I'm only
thinking about myself...

00:12:17.380 --> 00:12:18.420
And I hate that.

00:12:23.860 --> 00:12:25.540
I'm afraid that if this keeps up...

00:12:27.530 --> 00:12:31.640
I won't even be able
to stand being near you.

00:13:03.670 --> 00:13:04.670
I understand.

00:13:06.330 --> 00:13:07.690
Let's take some space for a while.

00:13:16.070 --> 00:13:17.820
Because I don't want to see you cry.

00:13:19.790 --> 00:13:21.360
Let's just be regular friends

00:13:22.210 --> 00:13:24.000
and rethink what we should do.

00:13:30.160 --> 00:13:31.730
You need to think about it too, Wataru.

00:13:40.540 --> 00:13:41.940
I've already made up my mind.

00:13:42.060 --> 00:13:43.350
Even so, think about it again.

00:13:45.610 --> 00:13:47.680
Don't think about what happened with other
people.

00:13:48.790 --> 00:13:50.710
Think about what's between the two of us.

00:13:59.960 --> 00:14:00.960
Okay.

00:14:03.520 --> 00:14:04.520
I will.

00:14:06.690 --> 00:14:08.050
I'll really think about it.

00:14:33.190 --> 00:14:35.280
Wataru cried.

00:14:38.620 --> 00:14:40.140
Even though we both feel the same way,

00:14:41.340 --> 00:14:43.490
he's so determined to
stay within the "friend" box.

00:14:48.240 --> 00:14:49.810
It's not about being friends.

00:14:50.410 --> 00:14:52.300
And it's not about being lovers.

00:14:54.190 --> 00:14:58.350
Can't Wataru and I just be together
in whatever way we want?

00:15:03.620 --> 00:15:06.080
He's just so important to me.

00:15:25.990 --> 00:15:26.990
Grandpa?

00:15:27.340 --> 00:15:28.340
What's up?

00:15:29.530 --> 00:15:30.530
Minato.

00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:32.760
Could you come home for a bit?

00:15:49.320 --> 00:15:52.180
You called so suddenly,
I thought something had happened.

00:15:53.480 --> 00:15:54.870
Even if nothing's wrong,

00:15:55.820 --> 00:15:57.280
I still want to see my grandson.

00:15:58.580 --> 00:15:59.580
Thanks.

00:16:00.570 --> 00:16:02.160
Are you free today?

00:16:04.910 --> 00:16:06.590
Lately, even on your days off,

00:16:07.750 --> 00:16:09.080
you always seem so busy.

00:16:10.570 --> 00:16:11.570
I guess so.

00:16:12.570 --> 00:16:15.590
I thought maybe you were out on a date.

00:16:19.160 --> 00:16:20.780
You could always invite Wataru

00:16:21.420 --> 00:16:22.780
to go out somewhere with you.

00:16:25.320 --> 00:16:26.320
Actually,

00:16:26.420 --> 00:16:28.660
Wataru said he wanted
to see you too, Grandpa.

00:16:30.090 --> 00:16:31.090
That's nice to hear.

00:16:33.190 --> 00:16:34.560
Only Grandpa?

00:16:35.240 --> 00:16:37.060
Of course he wants to see Grandma too.

00:16:37.250 --> 00:16:38.960
Then it's all OK.

00:16:39.240 --> 00:16:40.250
OK.

00:16:44.250 --> 00:16:45.450
What's that you've got there?

00:16:46.550 --> 00:16:47.780
Grandma gave it to me.

00:16:48.470 --> 00:16:50.480
She said since I'm always taking pictures,

00:16:52.070 --> 00:16:54.100
I can use this to put them
in an album right away.

00:16:54.990 --> 00:16:57.660
And I can jot down a few notes too.

00:17:03.850 --> 00:17:04.850
Grandpa,

00:17:05.210 --> 00:17:08.040
you really have been taking
photos of Grandma forever.

00:17:10.010 --> 00:17:13.620
I've been using
it since I was little.

00:17:13.930 --> 00:17:15.570
You really take good care of your things.

00:17:16.330 --> 00:17:17.830
Because it's important to me.

00:17:18.970 --> 00:17:20.110
Important?

00:17:20.940 --> 00:17:22.170
When something is important,

00:17:22.380 --> 00:17:24.180
wouldn't you be lonely if you lost it?

00:17:24.480 --> 00:17:25.860
Yeah...

00:17:26.910 --> 00:17:31.970
How to make sure it stays by your side forever
is something you have to really consider.

00:17:35.710 --> 00:17:36.710
You two!

00:17:36.920 --> 00:17:38.500
Tea is ready.

00:17:38.870 --> 00:17:41.070
I bought those sweets you like, Minato.

00:17:41.700 --> 00:17:43.450
Come and have some.

00:17:43.990 --> 00:17:44.990
Okay.

00:17:45.090 --> 00:17:47.310
Only Minato gets sweets?

00:17:47.810 --> 00:17:50.480
Grandpa, aren't you
banned from eating sugar?

00:17:51.130 --> 00:17:52.330
Right, right.

00:17:54.540 --> 00:17:56.210
Grandpa, are you feeling okay?

00:17:57.890 --> 00:18:00.170
My last checkup had a few red flags.

00:18:01.020 --> 00:18:02.350
The follow-up results

00:18:02.420 --> 00:18:03.680
turned out fine,

00:18:04.710 --> 00:18:06.580
but Grandma was still worried.

00:18:08.090 --> 00:18:10.560
Grandma really cares about you, Grandpa.

00:18:13.310 --> 00:18:14.540
I hope so.

00:18:17.470 --> 00:18:18.850
Grandpa,

00:18:19.640 --> 00:18:21.210
what is Grandma to you?

00:18:21.300 --> 00:18:24.900
(Everything fades with an "OK")

00:18:24.960 --> 00:18:26.870
She's the person who's closest to me,

00:18:27.560 --> 00:18:28.760
and the most important.

00:18:29.970 --> 00:18:31.170
Closest?

00:18:32.640 --> 00:18:34.129
Because I've been right there,

00:18:34.130 --> 00:18:37.660
watching her life unfold up close.

00:18:39.840 --> 00:18:42.950
And the one who's been closest to my life

00:18:43.400 --> 00:18:44.400
is Grandma.

00:18:46.620 --> 00:18:48.010
To me,

00:18:49.230 --> 00:18:52.180
that's true happiness.

00:18:59.040 --> 00:19:03.120
Put the camera back in the dry box for me.

00:19:03.660 --> 00:19:04.660
Okay.

00:19:04.680 --> 00:19:05.680
I will.

00:19:11.080 --> 00:19:12.770
Right there, up close?

00:19:14.030 --> 00:19:15.030
Yeah.

00:19:15.880 --> 00:19:16.880
Ah.

00:19:24.380 --> 00:19:25.380
Minato.

00:19:25.460 --> 00:19:26.460
Let's go.

00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:35.840
I...

00:19:36.120 --> 00:19:39.020
I want to be up close,
watching Wataru smile forever.

00:19:49.830 --> 00:19:51.030
Minato!

00:19:51.590 --> 00:19:55.020
Your grandpa is about to steal your sweets!

00:19:55.500 --> 00:19:56.500
I'm coming!

00:20:01.580 --> 00:20:03.000
If I want to make that happen...

00:20:06.500 --> 00:20:11.300
(September 27, 2025)

00:20:16.630 --> 00:20:18.920
Oh, that's perfect. Very natural.

00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:21.040
You look great.

00:20:23.980 --> 00:20:24.980
Thanks.

00:20:26.500 --> 00:20:27.970
Let me switch lenses.

00:20:31.590 --> 00:20:32.590
Hey.

00:20:33.280 --> 00:20:34.280
This bouquet...

00:20:34.720 --> 00:20:37.200
It's the same as the one you
gave me when you proposed, right?

00:20:37.510 --> 00:20:39.500
- But did you upgrade it?
- Yeah.

00:20:39.740 --> 00:20:41.460
I asked the florist to make it even better.

00:20:41.800 --> 00:20:43.520
Pretty impressive that I remembered, right?

00:20:43.730 --> 00:20:45.430
Yeah, yeah, very impressive.

00:20:45.470 --> 00:20:47.370
You're being so dismissive.

00:20:48.330 --> 00:20:50.720
You were crying your eyes out back then.

00:20:51.210 --> 00:20:54.540
Because you said you
wanted to be with me forever.

00:20:55.050 --> 00:20:57.010
You were crying too!

00:20:57.410 --> 00:20:59.170
I was so nervous.

00:21:00.370 --> 00:21:02.630
At Gotanda Station during rush hour,

00:21:02.640 --> 00:21:04.520
the two of us were just
standing there sobbing.

00:21:05.200 --> 00:21:06.850
Oh, it was at the station?

00:21:07.820 --> 00:21:09.130
Our date was over,

00:21:09.160 --> 00:21:12.870
and I just couldn't stand the
thought of us going home separately.

00:21:13.140 --> 00:21:15.440
Before I knew it, I was
standing in front of a florist.

00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:17.050
I was happy,

00:21:17.340 --> 00:21:18.890
but it was so embarrassing.

00:21:19.540 --> 00:21:21.060
There were so many people around.

00:21:21.640 --> 00:21:23.810
Right by the ticket gates...

00:21:24.120 --> 00:21:25.400
It was in front of the lockers!

00:21:25.950 --> 00:21:28.160
I tried to find somewhere quiet,

00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:29.519
but it was packed.

00:21:29.520 --> 00:21:31.070
Everyone was staring.

00:21:32.760 --> 00:21:33.760
You know,

00:21:34.780 --> 00:21:37.980
thinking about the wedding being
so close makes me emotional.

00:21:38.910 --> 00:21:40.309
For the wedding next month,

00:21:40.310 --> 00:21:43.710
we want to display all
the photos we took today.

00:21:44.120 --> 00:21:46.850
Then I'll make sure to get
some great shots for you.

00:21:50.020 --> 00:21:51.300
Oh, Kazuma.

00:21:51.680 --> 00:21:52.680
Your bowtie.

00:22:04.940 --> 00:22:06.660
Alright, let's get ready for the next shot.

00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:10.720
I want that too.

00:22:11.350 --> 00:22:13.070
I want to be by Minato's side forever.

00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:20.920
I...

00:22:23.060 --> 00:22:24.260
What do I really want to do?

00:22:24.500 --> 00:22:29.400
(September 28, 2025)

00:22:34.500 --> 00:22:39.000
(Minato: I have something to tell you.)

00:23:00.350 --> 00:23:02.346
(Next Episode Preview)
I want to cherish these feelings.

00:23:02.370 --> 00:23:03.710
We're best friends.

00:23:03.920 --> 00:23:04.590
Huh?

00:23:04.591 --> 00:23:06.989
I'm the one who said
we should be best friends.

00:23:06.990 --> 00:23:09.239
Let's not see each other for a while.

00:23:09.240 --> 00:23:10.830
It's not too late.

00:23:10.960 --> 00:23:11.960
Minato?

00:23:12.050 --> 00:23:14.560
Because I can't stop
myself from loving you.